IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: CONNECT ELEVATES ENTREPRENEURS BY PROVIDING EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMMING, MENTORSHIP, INTRODUCTIONS, AND ACCESS TO CAPITAL. WE HELP INNOVATIVE COMPANIES THRIVE SO THEY CAN MAKE A MEANINGFUL IMPACT IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE SAN DIEGO REGION. WE'RE ON A MISSION TO BUILD A WORLD-CLASS INNOVATION ECONOMY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: CONNECT IS AN INNOVATION INSTIGATOR ESTABLISHED TO CULTIVATE SAN DIEGO'S LIFE SCIENCE AND TECH COMMUNITIES. A TRUSTED PARTNER FOR MORE THAN 30 YEARS, WE PROPEL OUR REGION'S ENTREPRENEURS AS THEY CREATE AND SCALE THEIR COMPANIES FROM FIRST-TIME FOUNDERS TO SEASONED EXECUTIVES. WE OPERATE ACROSS DIVERSE INDUSTRY VERTICALS WITH A MINDSET DRIVEN BY INCLUSIVE SOCIAL GOOD MAKING A POSITIVE IMPACT ACROSS THE ENTIRETY OF THE MEGA-REGION. IN ELEVATING ENTREPRENEURIAL MASTERY SUCH AS PROVIDING ACCESS TO INSTITUTIONAL CAPITAL, STRATEGIC ADVISING, AND PARTNERING OPPORTUNITIES WE BRING TOGETHER OUR REGION'S CULTURE AND SPIRIT TO IGNITE OUR INNOVATION ECONOMY.
IRS990.Desc: LIFE SCIENCE LUMINARY DINNER, AN ANNUAL DINNER OF KEY PLAYERS IN THE SAN DIEGO LIFE SCIENCE COMMUNITY, TRADITIONALLY HOSTED AT THE HOME OF A SUCCESSFUL LIFE SCIENCE ENTREPRENEUR THAT MADE GREAT STRIDES IN THE LIFE SCIENCE COMMUNITY IN THE PAST YEAR. THE DINNER BRINGS IN ONLY THE TOP INNOVATORS TO BUILD RELATIONSHIPS, NETWORK, AND CELEBRATE THE SAN DIEGO LIFE SCIENCE COMMUNITY

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: COOL COMPANIESCOOL COMPANIES PRIVATE EVENT, AN ANNUAL PROGRAM WHERE CONNECT SELECTS THE TOP CENTURE CAPITAL-READY TECHNOLOGY AND LIFE SCIENCE COMPANIES TO BE NAMED A "COOL COMPANY". ALL THE COMPANIES' CEOS MEET INVESTORS IN A PRIVATE INVITE-ONLY EVENT WITH THE INTENTION OF SECURING FUNDING FOR THEIR COMPANY;COOL COMPANIES PUBLIC EVENT, AN ANNUAL GATHERING FOR THE SAN DIEGO COMMUNITY TO MEET AND LEARN ABOUT EACH COOL COMPANY, AS WELL AS NETWORK, MAKE RELATIONSHIPS, AND CELEBRATE THE NEW COOL COMPANIES;VC ROAD TRIP, DURING DAY 2 OF THE COOL COMPANIES PRIVATE EVENT, VENTURE CAPITALISTS FROM ALL AROUND THE COUNTRY EMBARK ON AN OUTING, TYPICALLY SAILING, AND ARE GIVEN A TOUR OF SAN DIEGO. THE PURPOSE OF THE DAY LEARN ABOUT SAN DIEGO AND TO GROW RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN OUT-OF-TOWN VENTURE CAPITALISTS AND THE SAN DIEGO INNOVATION COMMUNITY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: OFFICE HOURS, PROVIDES ENTREPRENEURS AN OPPORTUNITY FOR PRIVATE, PRO BONO PROFESSIONAL ADVICE;

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONNECT FOUNDATION USES A LOSS CONTINGENCIES APPROACH FOR EVALUATING UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND CONTINUALLY EVALUATES CHANGES IN TAX LAW AND NEW AUTHORITATIVE RULINGS.

FIVE.TEN.THIRTY WAS THE LARGEST GATHERING OF THE INNOVATION COMMUNITY IN SAN DIEGO HISTORY. CONNECT GATHERED 200 VCS, ANGEL INVESTORS, CEOS, CTOS, DEI LEADERS, NATIONAL SECURITY LEADERS, AND 160+ TECH AND LIFE SCIENCE COMPANIES, DRIVING INNOVATION ACROSS SAN DIEGO TO CONTINUE COLLECTIVE MOMENTUM FORWARD TO SCALING UP A MORE ROBUST AND MORE INCLUSIVE ECONOMY ACROSS THE MEGAREGION. OVER 3,000 PEOPLE ATTENDED THIS INAUGURAL EVENT. THE GOALS OF 5.10.30 ARE TO CELEBRATE COMMUNITY ADVANCEMENT, TO GENERATE INTEREST OUTSIDE OF SAN DIEGO AND ATTRACT MORE TALENT TO SAN DIEGO; SPRINGBOARD, A BUSINESS CREATION AND DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM IN WHICH BUSINESS ADVISORS PROVIDE MENTORSHIP TO NEW TECHNOLOGY COMPANIES WHO THEN PRESENT TO A PANEL OF INDUSTRY VETERANS, INVESTORS AND SERVICE PROVIDERS; FRAMEWORKS WORKSHOPS, HALF-DAY, PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS STRUCTURED TO PROVIDE AN OVERVIEW OF BUSINESS BASICS THROUGH 'FUNDAMENTALS': A VOCABULARY, FOUNDATION AND 'FRAMEWORK' IN WHICH BUSINESS LEADERSHIP CAN BE BUILT AROUND, AND 'ADVANCED WORKSHOPS': A FOCUSED AND DETAILED LOOK AT SPECIALIZED AND INDUSTRY SPECIFIC TOPICS CUSTOMIZED TO FIT THE NEEDS OF A START-UP COMPANY; CONNECT INNOVATION REPORT, A REGIONAL QUARTERLY INDEX WHICH TRACKS THE HEALTH OF THE SAN DIEGO INNOVATION ECONOMY BY COMPARING DATA YEAR TO YEAR AND QUARTER TO QUARTER, PROVIDING A COMPARISON ACROSS TECH INDUSTRY CLUSTERS TO SELECTED REGIONS AND MONITORING AVAILABILITY OF VARIOUS TYPES OF CAPITAL. THE DATA HELPS POLICYMAKERS AND TRADE ORGANIZATIONS PLAN AND ADVOCATE EFFECTIVELY FOR INNOVATION ECONOMY INCLUDING AVAILABILITY OF VISAS AND WORKFORCE TRAINING FOR TALENT IN HIGH GROWTH CLUSTERS, BUILDING AN ATTRACTIVE ENVIRONMENT FOR CAPITAL INVESTMENT, ALLOCATION OF GRANT FUNDING, REFORM OF THE PATENT SYSTEM AND ZONING; SUMMER SOCIAL, AN ANNUAL GATHERING OF SAN DIEGO ENTREPRENEURS, INNOVATORS, INVESTORS, CEOS, AND SERVICE PROVIDERS GETTING TOGETHER TO NETWORK, MAKE RELATIONSHIPS, AND CELEBRATE THE INNOVATION COMMUNITY OF SAN DIEGO. THE PROGRAM WILL RESUME IN FISCAL YEAR 2023 (JULY 2022); MEET A MENTOR, A PROGRAM THAT MATCHES EARLY-STAGE COMPANIES WITH GENERALIST MENTORS TO ANSWER QUESTIONS RANGING FROM IDEAS, BUSINESS PLANS, MARKETING, AND MORE; VC ROAD TRIP, DURING DAY 2 OF THE COOL COMPANIES PRIVATE EVENT, VENTURE CAPITALISTS FROM ALL AROUND THE COUNTRY EMBARK ON AN OUTING, TYPICALLY SAILING, AND ARE GIVEN A TOUR OF SAN DIEGO. THE PURPOSE OF THE DAY LEARN ABOUT SAN DIEGO AND TO GROW RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN OUT-OF-TOWN VENTURE CAPITALISTS AND THE SAN DIEGO INNOVATION COMMUNITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS FIRST REVIEWED BY THE ORGANIZATION'S ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT AND AUDIT COMMITTEE WHERE IT IS COMPARED AGAINST AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. FORM 990 IS THEN FORWARDED TO THE CEO FOR HIS REVIEW, WITH EMPHASIS ON NON-FINANCIAL INFORMATION CONTAINED IN THE TAX RETURN. ONCE AUTHORIZED BY THE CEO, THE FORM 990 IS SENT TO THE AUDIT COMMITTEE FOR APPROVAL. ONCE APPROVED, IT IS DISTRIBUTED TO THE FULL BOARD FOR COMMENTS. LASTLY, THE TAX PREPARER IS NOTIFIED THAT THE FORM 990 IS READY TO BE FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WHEN A PERCEIVED CONFLICT EXISTS AND IS NOT RAISED, IT IS ADDRESSED WITH THE INDIVIDUAL AND THE INDIVIDUAL IS ASKED TO ABSTAIN FROM VOTING OR PERFORMING ACTIONS THAT WOULD CREATE A CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE MADE UP OF EXECUTIVES FROM VARIOUS PROFESSIONS EVALUATE THE CEO'S SALARY ANNUALLY. THEY COMPARE HIS SALARY TO COMPARABLE NON-PROFIT COMPANIES IN THE REGION USING THE "CHARITY NAVIGATOR CEO COMPENSATION STUDY" THE CEO'S SALARY IS ADJUSTED UPWARD BASED ON MEETING CERTAIN MILESTONES, AND CAN BE DEFERRED UPON AGREEMENT BY THE CEO AND THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST. THE FORM 990 IS ALSO AVAILABLE ON WWW.GUIDESTAR.COM.

THERE HAVE BEEN NO CHANGES FROM THE PRIOR YEAR BY ORGANIZATION'S COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES RESPONSIBLITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT.
